Facing the sun
Given an array representng heights of buildings.
You have to  count the buildings which will see the sunrise (Assume:Sun rise on the side of array starting point).

Sample Input:
5
6 2 7 4 10
Sample Output:
3

import java.util.*;
class Buildings
{
public static void main(String args[])
{
Scanner s= new Scanner(System.in);
int n=s.nextInt();
int a[]=new int[n];
int c=1;
for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
a[i]=s.nextInt();
}
int max=a[0];
for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
if(a[i]>max)
c++;
}
System.out.print(c);

}
}
